msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:10
msgid "Blender 2.5 with a Big Buck Bunny scene open"
msgstr "Blender 2.5 版中被打开的大雄兔电影场景"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:12
msgid "Welcome to Blender, the free and open source 3D animation suite."
msgstr "欢迎加入Blender 这个免费开源的3D动画创作套件的使用者行列，"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:14
msgid ""
"Blender can be used to create 3D visualizations such as still images, video "
"and real-time interactive video games."
msgstr "Blender可以创作多种3D视觉内容，比如图像，视频，实时交互的视频游戏等。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:16
msgid ""
"Blender is well suited to individuals and small studios who benefit from "
"its unified pipeline and responsive development process."
msgstr ""
"Blender 非常适合中小型工作室和独立制作人使用，因为它的工作流统一，几乎可以在"
"同一软件中完成所有的3D项目工作，而且有着非常迅速可靠的开发支持。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:19
msgid ""
"It is cross-platform and runs on Linux, Mac-OSX and MS-Windows systems with "
"a small memory and disk footprint. Its interface uses OpenGL to provide a "
"consistent experience across all supported hardware and platforms."
msgstr ""
"Blender在Linux，mac和windows这三个平台上都同样的运行良好，对机器内存和硬盘的"
"要求也不太高。由于使用了OpenGL来作为界面的底层库，在支持这些库的硬件和操作系"
"统平台上给予了用户非常一致性的用户体验。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:24
msgid "Key Features"
msgstr "主要功能"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:26
msgid ""
"Blender is a fully integrated 3D content creation suite, offering a broad "
"range of essential tools, including :doc:`Modeling </modeling/"
"introduction>`, :ref:`UV Mapping <editors-uv_image-index>`, :doc:`Texturing "
"</editors/uv_image/texturing/introduction>`, :doc:`Rigging </rigging/"
"introduction>`, :doc:`Animation </animation/introduction>`, many types of :"
"doc:`Simulations </physics/introduction>`, :doc:`Scripting </advanced/"
"scripting/introduction>`, :doc:`Rendering </render/introduction>`, :doc:"
"`Compositing </compositing/introduction>`, :doc:`VFX </editors/"
"movie_clip_editor/index>`, and :doc:`Game Creation </game_engine/"
"introduction>`."
msgstr ""
"Blender是一套完整集成的3D创作套件，提供了全面的必要创作工具，包括 :doc:`建模"
"（modeling） </modeling/introduction>`, :ref:`uv映射（uv-mapping） <editors-"
"uv_image-index>`, :doc:`纹理（texturing） </editors/uv_image/texturing/"
"introduction>`, :doc:`骨骼装配（rigging）和蒙皮（skinning） </rigging/"
"introduction>`, :doc:`动画（animation） </animation/introduction>`, 多种类型"
"的 :doc:`模拟 </physics/introduction>` (流体、刚体等等), :doc:`脚本 </"
"advanced/scripting/introduction>`, :doc:`渲染 </render/introduction>`, :doc:"
"`合成 </composite_nodes/introduction>`, :doc:`后期特效 </editors/"
"movie_clip_editor/index>`, 和 :doc:`游戏创作 </game_engine/introduction>` 。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:38
msgid ""
"Cross platform, with an OpenGL GUI that is uniform on all major platforms "
"(and customizable with Python scripts)."
msgstr ""
"跨平台，使用OpenGL的GUI，在所有主流平台上显示效果一致（可通过Python脚本来定"
"制化界面）。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:39
msgid ""
"High quality 3D architecture enabling fast and efficient creation work-flow."
msgstr "高质量的3D架构带来了快速高效的创作流程。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:40
msgid ""
"Excellent community support from `forums <http://BlenderArtists.org>`__ "
"and :ref:`IRC <irc-channels>`."
msgstr ""
"非常棒的用户社区支持 `forums <http://BlenderArtists.org>`__ and :ref:`IRC "
"<irc-channels>`."

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:41
msgid "Small executable size, optionally portable."
msgstr "小巧的体积，便于分发。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:43
msgid ""
"You can download the latest version of Blender `here <http://www.blender."
"org/download/>`__."
msgstr ""
"你可以在 `这里 <http://www.blender.org/download/>`_ 下载最新版Blender。 "

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:48
msgid "A rendered image being post-processed"
msgstr "正在被后期处理的已经渲染的图像"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:51
msgid ""
"Blender makes it possible to perform a wide range of tasks, and it may seem "
"daunting when first trying to grasp the basics. However, with a bit of "
"motivation and the right learning material, it is possible to familiarize "
"yourself with Blender after a few hours of practice."
msgstr ""
"Blender可以做非常宽广范围的工作任务，第一次拿着它的时候会有那么一点点胆怯。"
"但是，只需要有一点点的兴趣和找到对的教程材料。（Blender中文视频集：http://i."
"youku.com/u/UMTgzMTA0NDc2MA）就可以通过个把小时的训练熟悉Blender的操作了。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:55
msgid ""
"This manual is a good start, though it serves more as a reference. There "
"are also many online video tutorials from specialized websites, and several "
"books and training DVDs available in the `Blender Store <http://www.store."
"blender.org>`__ and on the `Blender Cloud <https://cloud.blender.org/>`__."
msgstr ""
"本手册是一个良好的开端，但它提供更多的参考。也有来自专业网站的许多在线视频教"
"程，和一些书籍和培训的DVD可以在  `Blender 网店 <http://www.store.blender."
"org>`__ 和在 `Blender 云服务 <https://cloud.blender.org/>`__."

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:60
msgid ""
"Despite everything Blender can do, it remains a tool. Great artists do not "
"create masterpieces by pressing buttons or manipulating brushes, but by "
"learning and practicing subjects such as human anatomy, composition, "
"lighting, animation principles, etc."
msgstr ""
"尽管Blender可以做非常多的事情，不过它仍然是一个工具。一位艺术大师不可能就通"
"过按几个按钮或者随便刷几笔就做出惊人的艺术作品来，他们的作品都是通过平常的练"
"习积累以及思考，练习包括：人体结构，合成，灯光，动画原理还有相当的计算机知"
"识。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:64
msgid ""
"3D content creation software such as Blender have the added technical "
"complexity and jargon associated with the underlying technologies. Terms "
"like UV maps, materials, shaders, meshes, and subsurf are the mediums of "
"the digital artist, and understanding them, even broadly, will help you to "
"use Blender to its best."
msgstr ""
"像Blender这样的3D内容创作工具软件，还有相当多的计算机相关的技术知识是需要了"
"解的。比如UV贴图，材质，着色器，细分曲面都是数字艺术家表达思想的媒介，更好的"
"理解这甚至更多更广泛的些技术，可以帮助艺术家们更好的使用Blender。"

#: ../../manual/getting_started/about_blender/introduction.rst:69
msgid ""
"So keep reading this manual, learn the great tool that Blender is, keep "
"your mind open to other artistic and technological areas, and you too can "
"become a great artist."
msgstr ""
"请继续阅读这套手册，学习更多的Blender里面的工具功能，开放自己的思维，多学习"
"其他艺术家和其他的技术领域，我相信每位手册的读者也能成为一位伟大的艺术家。"
